Teatime commuters travelling from Glasgow faced six miles of slow moving traffic at Cumbernauld.A police spokeswoman said a two car crash northbound on the M80 between Glasgow and Cumbernauld had caused traffic to slow down and led to delays.The accident happened at junction six at the Old Inns at 5.20pm.One motorist said: &quot;it usually takes me about half an hour to get home to Cumbernauld bit tonight it was nearly an hour.&quot;